{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Bacterial Disulfide bond forming (Dsb) proteins facilitate proper folding and disulfide bond formation of periplasmic and secreted proteins [[cite:PUB00080832]].</p>\n \n<p>Thiol:disulphide interchange proteins DsbA and DsbL are involved in disulfide-bond formation [[cite:PUB00014003], [cite:PUB00080831]]. They act by transferring its disulfide bond to other proteins and are reduced in the process. DsbA is required for disulfide bond formation in some periplasmic proteins such as PhoA or OmpA and is reoxidised by DsbB [[cite:PUB00068800], [cite:PUB00068801]].  DsbA is a monomeric thiol disulfide oxidoreductase protein containing a redox active CXXC motif imbedded in a TRX fold. It is involved in the oxidative protein folding pathway in prokaryotes, and is the strongest thiol oxidant known, due to the unusual stability of the thiolate anion form of the first cysteine in the CXXC motif [[cite:PUB00080835]]. The highly unstable oxidized form of DsbA directly donates disulfide bonds to reduced proteins secreted into the bacterial periplasm. This rapid and unidirectional process helps to catalyze the folding of newly-synthesized polypeptides. To regain catalytic activity, reduced DsbA is then reoxidized by the membrane protein DsbB, which generates its disulfides from oxidized quinones, which in turn are reoxidized by the electron transport chain [[cite:PUB00080833]].  DsbL is reoxidised by DsbI; DsbL and DsbI represent a second redox couple in some bacteria for specific substrates [[cite:PUB00050921]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "4dvc", "name" "Structural and functional studies of TcpG, the Vibrio cholerae DsbA disulfide-forming protein required for pilus and cholera toxin production"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR036249", "name" "Thioredoxin-like superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"cdd" {"cd03019" "DsbA_DsbA"}, "pirsf" {"PIRSF001488" "Thiol:disulphide interchange protein"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Thiol:disulphide interchange protein DsbA/DsbL", "short" "DsbA/DsbL"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 266, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 1786, "taxa" 8398, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 12208, "sets" 0, "proteins" 12199, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 9448}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR023205", :literature {"PUB00050921" {"URL" nil, "issue" "4", "authors" ["Grimshaw JP" "Stirnimann CU" "Brozzo MS" "Malojcic G" "Grutter MG" "Capitani G" "Glockshuber R."], "ISO_journal" "J. Mol. Biol.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.jmb.2008.05.031", "medline_journal" "J Mol Biol", "title" "DsbL and DsbI form a specific dithiol oxidase system for periplasmic arylsulfate sulfotransferase in uropathogenic Escherichia coli.", "year" 2008, "raw_pages" "667-80", "volume" "380", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 18565543}, "PUB00014003" {"URL" nil, "issue" nil, "authors" ["Kadokura H" "Katzen F" "Beckwith J."], "ISO_journal" "Annu. Rev. Biochem.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1146/annurev.biochem.72.121801.161459", "medline_journal" "Annu Rev Biochem", "title" "Protein disulfide bond formation in prokaryotes.", "year" 2003, "raw_pages" "111-35", "volume" "72", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 12524212}, "PUB00080831" {"URL" nil, "issue" "1", "authors" ["Collet JF" "Bardwell JC."], "ISO_journal" "Mol. Microbiol.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1046/j.1365-2958.2002.02851.x", "medline_journal" "Mol Microbiol", "title" "Oxidative protein folding in bacteria.", "year" 2002, "raw_pages" "1-8", "volume" "44", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 11967064}, "PUB00080833" {"URL" nil, "issue" "5657", "authors" ["Kadokura H" "Tian H" "Zander T" "Bardwell JC" "Beckwith J."], "ISO_journal" "Science", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1126/science.1091724", "medline_journal" "Science", "title" "Sn